Cleaning spp names (must be IDd to species!)

#unique species names
spp_sa <- dat_SA[,unique(spp)]


#Using taxize package, I'm going to check and standardize species scientific names
result.long <- spp_sa %>%
gnr_resolve(data_source_ids = c(9,155), #marine species and fisebase sources
            with_canonical_ranks=T)

result.long <- data.table(result.long)

# be sure to keep these with randomly  low scores, otherwise, score about 75 is good
#Peprilus triacanthus

#delete repeats and get weird of weird ones

result.short <- result.long[result.long[, .I[which.max(score)], by=.(user_supplied_name, matched_name2)]$V1][,spp := user_supplied_name][score > 0.75 | matched_name2 %in% c("Peprilus triacanthus"),]

#merge cleaned species names with neus full 
dat_SA.clean <- dat_SA[result.short, on = "spp"]

Now, well overlay grid cells onto this list of tows (dat_sa) using lat and lon and gridrr package


year_grid <- data.table(table(dat_SA.clean$cell, dat_SA.clean$year))

#there are some grid cells with infrequent records, I will delete these
grid_cells_to_exclude <- unique(year_grid[N == 0]$V1)

#delete these grid cells from full data table
dat_sa.reduced <- dat_SA.clean[!cell %in% grid_cells_to_exclude]

#362516 observations left, this should be great

#how many tows (TOW) per cell in a given year

haul_cell_unique <- unique(dat_sa.reduced[,.(haulid, cell, year)])

sa_samplingevents_byyear <- haul_cell_unique[,.N, .(year, cell)]

sa_cells_lessthan3 <- sa_samplingevents_byyear[N<3,]

cells_to_delete <- unique(sa_cells_lessthan3[,cell])

dat_sa.reduced.again <- dat_sa.reduced[!cell %in% cells_to_delete]

#down to 192500 observations

saveRDS(dat_sa.reduced.again, "sa_data_gridded.rds")

Find distance between center of each grid cell

#just need grid cell # and center lat lon for each grid cell 
sa_grid_cells <- unique(dat_sa.reduced.again[,.(cell, LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

sa_grid_cells <- setorder(sa_grid_cells, cell)

sa_reg_distances <- distm(sa_grid_cells[,.(LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

colnames(sa_reg_distances) <- sa_grid_cells$cell
rownames(sa_reg_distances) <- sa_grid_cells$cell

#reorient to long form 
sa_reg_distances.l <- melt(as.matrix(sa_reg_distances), varnames = c("cell1", "cell2"), value.name = "distance(m)") #matrix to data frame
The melt generic in data.table has been passed a matrix and will attempt to redirect to the relevant reshape2 method; please note that reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well. To continue using melt methods from reshape2 while both libraries are attached, e.g. melt.list, you can prepend the namespace like reshape2::melt(as.matrix(sa_reg_distances)). In the next version, this warning will become an error.
sa_reg_distances.l <- data.table(sa_reg_distances.l) #and then to data table
sa_reg_distances.l <- sa_reg_distances.l[cell1 > cell2,] # get rid of repetitions and self-comparisons
saveRDS(sa_reg_distances.l, "sa_reg_distances.l.rds")
